{{Quote|I've been very fortunate to have Mich at the helm of my company. She has provided the focus and strategy needed to keep Lucasfilm at the forefront of the global entertainment industry. Mich has been a key member of my executive team for over 20-years and she will be missed. I wish her the best in her retirement.|[[George Lucas]]|<ref name="The Wrap">{{WebCite|url=https://www.thewrap.com/lucasfilm-coo-president-micheline-chau-retires-54891|text=Lucasfilm COO, President Micheline Chau Retires - TheWrap|author=Shaw, Lucas|date=2012-09-05, 5:30 pm|work=[http://www.thewrap.com TheWrap]|archivedate=20200316005918}}</ref>}}
'''Micheline Chau''' served as President and Chief Operating Officer of [[Lucasfilm]] from [[April]] [[2003]] to [[September]] [[2012]] and served previously as Lucasfilm's Chief Financial Officer from [[1991]] to [[March]] 2003.<ref name="Equilar" /> Her retirement from Lucasfilm coincided with [[The Walt Disney Company]]'s purchase of Lucasfilm in late 2012,<ref name="Bloomberg-Chau">{{WebCite|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/profile/person/5486116|text=Micheline Chau: Executive Profile & Biography - Businessweek|work=[http://www.businessweek.com Bloomberg Businessweek]|archivedate=20201004101007}}</ref><ref name="Bloomberg-Lucasfilm">{{WebCite|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/profile/company/16426Z:US|text=Lucasfilm Ltd. LLC: Private Company Information - Businessweek|work=[http://www.businessweek.com Bloomberg Businessweek]|archivedate=20200202161635}}</ref> when [[Kathleen Kennedy]] assumed Chau's position.<ref name="The Wrap" /> Since [[February]] [[2013]], Chau has served as a board member of [[Wikipedia:Dolby Laboratories|Dolby Laboratories]], and in [[October]] [[2014]], she joined the board of [[Wikipedia:Las Vegas Sands|Las Vegas Sands Corp.]]<ref name="Equilar" />

Chau is credited with maintaining the vitality of the ''[[Star Wars]]'' franchise, Lucasfilm's primary asset, during her tenure with the company. She oversaw all major ''Star Wars'' initiatives as company president, including the development and distribution of the ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'' television series.<ref name="Bio">{{WebCite|url=http://www.committee100.org/aboutus/member_bio.php?member_id=252|text=Bio|work=[http://committee100.org Committee of 100]|archivedate=20171029234606}}</ref>
